claim.claim-text:
1. A medical knife assembly, comprising: 
a neonatal clamping arrangement having a cutting blade pivotally attached thereto; 
a maternal clamping arrangement, said maternal clamping arrangement being releasably secured to said neonatal clamping arrangement by a plurality of shear pins; 
said shear pins being aligned in a parallel plane and perpendicular to said cutting blade to facilitate their shearing to affect separation of said neonatal clamping arrangement from said maternal clamping arrangement.

10. A medical knife assembly, comprising: 
an inner assembly having a cutting blade disposed between a pair of spaced apart independent inner clamping members, said cutting blade being temporarily secured in a ready for use position by an elongated blade shear pin extending through said pair of independent inner clamping members and said cutting blade; 
an outer assembly being pivotally mounted to said inner assembly and having a pair of spaced apart independent outer clamping members, said outer clamping members being releasably secured in the ready to use position by another elongated blade shear pin extending through said pair of independent outer clamping members; 
said pair of independent inner clamping members and said pair of outer clamping members being separable into a pair of inner and outer pairs for defining a neonatal clamp and a maternal clamp upon severance of both said elongated blade shear pin and said another elongated blade shear pin.

12. A method of clamping and severing an umbilical cord at time of birth, comprising: 
providing a medical knife assembly including: 
a neonatal clamping arrangement having a cutting blade pivotally attached thereto; 
a maternal clamping arrangement, said maternal clamping arrangement being releasably secured to said neonatal clamping arrangement by a plurality of shear pins; 
said shear pins being aligned in a parallel plane and perpendicular to said cutting blade to facilitate their shearing to affect separation of said neonatal clamping arrangement from said maternal clamping arrangement; 
grasping said medical knife assembly in one hand; and 
rotating said cutting blade pivotally to sever the umbilical cord and said plurality of shear pins, said rotation being sufficient to concurrently clamp the umbilical cord with said neonatal clamping arrangement on an infant side of the umbilical cord and with the maternal clamping arrangement on a mother side of the umbilical cord.
